Great food and tasty drinks. Our waitress Ashley was friendly. She gave us great tips for enjoying Nashville. The atmosphere adds to the Nashville culture. Loved the cream cheese and jelly!

I'm very stingy with the fifth star but this place nearly got it. We went here breakfast and the food was EXCELLENT.  Service was also very good and all contained in an old historic building which was really cool. I'll go back!

Excellent food, great service, and fair prices. The turkey and dressing was awesome! Homemade cranberry sauce was nice surprise. Went mid-afternoon on a Saturday and it was completely empty.

Good place

Great food. Great service. We have never had grits, the waiter brought us a sample. Potions were large and tasted simply amazing.

One of the best place I have eaten at in a very long time. The rattle snake chicken pasta had the wife wanting to go back in the kitchen to give the chef a kiss. The prime rib hash was just as good !! If you are new to town this is a most have before you leave to go back home.

Great service from our waitress, Rachel! Had some really good fried catfish and killer banana pudding to celebrate my birthday. My wife had a down home turkey and gravy dish that tasted just like Thanksgiving day!

Delicious food & great service. Very friendly. I had the blueberry pancakes with lemon curd & bacon. My husband had the farmer’s omelette with grits, biscuit & Jam. Both dishes were tasty. Highly recommend going there to eat.
Food and service was wonderful. Highly recommend!!!
Wonderful food and great staff! Would recommend to anyone!

Such a nice spot. Had music but it wasn’t obnoxiously loud. Great food, great service, good beer. 5 stars for sure.

Excellent place excellent food Rachel is an incredible person and great waitress she's engaging polite and respectful. I was fortunate enough to meet Anthony the owner also, a kind man, he has lot of pride in his work. I'll be back.
